  patient_primary_id STRING OPTIONS(description='The \'patient_primary_id\' field serves as the primary identifier for a patient within a healthcare system. It is crucial for linking all patient-related data, ensuring that healthcare providers have a complete and accurate view of the patient\'s medical history. This field is a key component of patient identity management and is considered sensitive information, as it can be used to access a patient\'s medical records.'),
  network_mnemonic STRING OPTIONS(description='The \'network_mnemonic\' field represents a shorthand or code used to identify a specific healthcare network. It is used for routing and managing data within and across healthcare systems, ensuring that information is directed to the correct network. This field is important for interoperability and efficient data exchange, but it does not contain patient-specific information.'),
